					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Like it a lot. Bizarre and quirky.</p> <p>I lost the thread a bit at</p> <blockquote> <p>SCP-2393-2-B is currently the only means of observing SCP-2393-3;</p> </blockquote> <p>because SCP-2393-3, later can only be observed within 10 meters of the main SCP (can't remember the designation: sometimes these suffixed SCP numbers really confuse me). What is the girl being observed on? With researchers' eyes, in the space around the juniper, or through the imaging program ..2-B?</p> <p>The files in Addendum 1 seemed to get a bit too tongue-in-cheek. But then you completely won me over with Addendum 2 (especially the song). Upvoted.</p> 
				 	]]>
