					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There's no small number of people around who can't tell 'new age' from 'witchcraft' from the outside. No reason to believe that trees would be any <em>less</em> conservative and reactionary than humans.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1147915#post-2250950</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1147915/scp-2393#post-2250950</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2015 03:15:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>HotCocoaNerd</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2032511</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The same could be asked as to how they have tech at all. Authorial headcanon assumes that at one point a dryad befriended a modern human, then got introduced to the interweb, then spread access to the interweb to other dryads, thus beginning the subculture. Then again, other interpretations are welcome. I agree that the technodryads might see themselves as new agey, but from the other dryads' perspective, this subculture just leaped into something that they have no idea what to think of. Pair that with Clarke's Third Law and BOOM, witchcraft.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
